---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import GeometryCanvas from '../../../components/diagrams/GeometryCanvas.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Area and Perimeter" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-5/" backLabel="← Grade 5">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Area and Perimeter</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Calculate rectangles, squares and their measurements</p>

	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>Perimeter vs. Area</h2>
		<p><strong>Perimeter</strong> = the length around the edge (how much fence do you need?)</p>
		<p><strong>Area</strong> = the space inside (how much grass do you need?)</p>

		<h3>🧪 Experiment: Changing Shapes</h3>
		<p>Drag the points and observe how the area changes. Can a triangle with the same perimeter have different areas?</p>
	</section>

	<GeometryCanvas client:visible />

	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 Key Formulas</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Rectangle:</strong> Perimeter = 2·(a+b), Area = a·b</li>
			<li><strong>Square:</strong> Perimeter = 4·a, Area = a·a = a²</li>
			<li><strong>Triangle:</strong> Area = (base × height) ÷ 2</li>
		</ul>
		<p>Surprise: Two shapes with the same perimeter can have completely different areas!</p>
	</section>
</Layout>
